<FIRST>r i AM-Nicaragua-Rebels     03-12 0202</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Nicaragua-Rebels,0210</SECOND>
<HEAD>Report Eight Killed in Rebel Attack on Village</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANAGUA, Nicaragua (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rebels attacked an eastern village
Saturday and in the battle six of the raiders and two local
officials were killed, the Sandinista government said.
   Terencio Lopez Marenco, the Sandinista party leader in the
village of Las Iguanas, 180 miles east of Managua, said two young
girls were wounded in the fighting early Saturday.
   He identified the slain government officials as 2nd Lt. Candido
Garcia, the village's civil defense chief, and Panfilo Lira, head of
the agricultural cooperative.
   Lopez Marenco said the rebels belonged to a group that recently
entered Nicaragua from Costa Rica.
   Last week the Defense Ministry accused rebel forces of making
more than 140 attacks against Nicaraguan military and civilian
targets this year in ``open violation of the cease-fire.''
   The rebels' radio station Radio Liberacion said Saturday that
Sandinista troops had violated the cease-fire 69 times in 1989.
   The Sandinistas and rebels agreed to a temporary cease-fire in
March 1988 but peace talks subsequently broke down. The government
then declared a monthly series of unilateral cease-fires beginning
in June 1988 and the insurgents tacitly accepted the truce.
   Both sides claim they have respected the cease-fires.
</TEXT>
