<HEAD>17 Killed As Soldiers Battle Communist Rebels</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Soldiers backed by helicopter gunships
battled communist guerrillas in a southern Philippine town, leaving
17 people dead, the military reported Sunday.
   The army report did not identify those killed Thursday in clashes
in Lupon town, 634 miles southeast of Manila.
   The first clash, with 50 New People's Army rebels, lasted two
hours, the report said. Thirty minutes later, other soldiers from
the same battalion encountered about 200 rebels near the same site,
it said.
