neighbor, police said.
   Kao Ayo, a secretary of the Tamano family, said Tamano had no
idea who planted the bomb. ``The senator said he has no enemies,''
she said.
   Tamano is one of two Moslems in the 23-member senate. Five
million of the country's 62 million people are Moslems living mostly
in the southern Philippines, where Moslem separatist guerrillas have
been fighting for self-rule for more than a decade.
