<SECOND>AM-Robber's Comeuppance,0213</SECOND>
<HEAD>81-Year-Old Bank Customer Socks It To Bank Robber</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An 81-year-old man struck a bank robber
with a karate-style chop after seeing him hit a female teller,
causing the robber to drop a bag of money and flee, authorities said.
   ``I don't believe in hitting ladies,'' said the elderly customer,
who asked not to be identified.
   The robber scooped up some $10 and $20 bills from the floor, but
left most of the money behind Friday as he ran out of a BancOhio
National Bank branch on the city's south side, said police Detective
Ted Shaw.
   Shaw said the robber handed a note demanding money to the teller
Friday afternoon. The robber said he had a gun, but no weapon was
seen, Shaw said.
   ``She (the teller) complied, but apparently it wasn't fast enough
for him,'' Shaw said. The robber struck the teller in the head with
the money-filled bag.
   That was when the elderly customer at the next window punched the
robber.
   ``I didn't give it a thought,'' the man said. ``I just hit that
man because he hit that woman.''
   Police refused to disclose the amount taken. No one had been
arrested in the robbery by early Sunday.
